---

<Base
  title="Arm Lift (Brachioplasty) in Houston Texas | The Oaks Plastic Surgery"
  description="Arm Lift (Brachioplasty) in Houston Texas at The Oaks Plastic Surgery. Board-certified plastic surgeons offering personalized care."
  headerTitle="Arm Lift (Brachioplasty) in Houston Texas"
  headerImage="/img/arm-lift-hero.jpg"
  headerMarginBottom={60}
  canonical="https://theoaksplasticsurgery.com/arm-lift-houston"
>
<section class="mb-0">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2">
                            <p class="wow fadeInUp lead text-center">
                                An Arm Lift helps to remove excess skin off the upper arms for a slimmer, sleeker contour.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-0">
                <div class="container-fluid">
                    
                </div>
            </section>            
            
            <section class="text-section pb-240">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <h2 class="wow fadeInUp center text-center"> </h2>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div data-jarallax-element="-140" class="text-section-box"></div>
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row text-row">
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Why to have an Arm Lift at The Oaks Plastic Surgery in Houston, Texas? </h3>
                                <p>
                                Many of our patients who have undergone massive weight loss or have developed excess arm skin with age are very self-conscious about this area. They complain that clothes don’t fit correctly, they are unable to wear short sleeves, and can have hygiene issues as well. Some patients simply desire a sleeker, tighter looking arm.  An arm lift can help you achieve this sleek contour and feel better about your arms in clothing with or without sleeves.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What do you want from an Arm Lift? </h3>
                                <p>
                                    Arm lift procedures are often a careful balance between scarring and contour.  While everyone’s goal is to maximize contour and minimize scarring, sometimes a trade off must exist.  The surgeons at The Oaks Plastic Surgery want to work with you to achieve your specific goals. If you are interested in an Arm Lift in Houston, Texas, an appointment can be made with Dr. Danielle Andry or Dr. Nandi Wijay.  You can expect the initial consultation to last an hour or more. In your consultation, your TOPS plastic surgeon will:

                                </p>
                                <p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Listen to your specific complaints and goals </li>
                                    <li>Perform a thorough examination, focusing on your individual anatomy and measurements</li>
                                    <li>Discuss recommendations regarding surgical or nonsurgical techniques that may help you achieve your goals</li>
                                    <li>If surgery is the right option for you, Dr. Danielle Andry or Dr. Nandi Wijay will discuss the details of the surgical procedures that are offered and which approach is right for you </li>
                                    <li>Preoperative photographs will be taken and the surgical plan will be analyzed for you with the use of your photographs </li>
                                    <li>The risks and benefits of surgery will be thoroughly outlined for you</li>
                                    <li>You will be given ample opportunity to ask questions from both our physicians and staff regarding the Arm Lift and any other surgical or nonsurgical procedures you may be interested in</li>
                                    <li>You will be sent home with a packet of information regarding the procedure including a detailed consent form and instructions for before and after the Arm Lift </li>
                                </ul>
                                </p>

                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-lg-6 pt-lg-5">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can you expect the day of your Arm Lift procedure? </h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    The day of your surgery, your TOPS plastic surgeon will meet you in the preoperative area to go over any last minute questions or concerns you may have.  They will make preoperative markings and will perform extensive checks with a focused attention to detail ensuring high quality care and safety.  You will meet the anesthesiologist and their team, as well as, the members of our operative team.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    During your cosmetic procedure, our TOPS plastic surgeons pay meticulous attention to detail and work as a team to ensure a great result with a focus on safety and quality.  Your family will be updated of your status periodically and will be able to talk with the physician one-on-one after the procedure is completed.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What procedures are often performed along with an Arm Lift?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    Many patients seeking an arm lift (brachioplasty) have undergone massive weight loss and require removal of excess skin from several areas of the body including the abdomen, thighs, back, breast, and face. <a href='/danielle-andry-houston'>Dr. Danielle Andry</a> and <a href='/nandi-wijay-houston'>Dr. Nandi Wijay</a>
 spend a large part of their training working with one of the innovators in breast contouring surgery after massive weight loss. They have experience in both staging and combining many of these massive weight loss, body contouring procedures and can counsel their patients on the timing and progression of these surgeries.  Please visit our massive weight loss, body contouring page for more details.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
